<subSubSection id="8DF971D4FFEA392D1A82FE2BFAC1FD64" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C55C225FFFEA392D1A82FE2BFAC1FD64" blockId="13.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D1A82FE2BFEB0FD8D" bold="true" box="[199,331,510,536]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">Discussion.</emphasis>
Females of this new species are very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="02E359DCFFEA392D1989FE2AFAF5FD8C" authority="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityYear="1984" box="[972,1294,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Macrurohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wirthi">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D1989FE2AFC18FD8D" box="[972,995,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D19B7FE2AFBCFFD8C" box="[1010,1076,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">wirthi</emphasis>
Spinelli &amp; Grogan
</taxonomicName>
, from which they can be distinguished by the distinctly longer distal flagellomeres in 
<taxonomicName id="02E359DCFFEA392D19FFFDF6FBDAFDA8" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityYear="1984" box="[954,1057,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Macrurohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wirthi">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D19FFFDF6FC2AFDA9" box="[954,977,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D199AFDF6FBDAFDA8" box="[991,1057,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">wirthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and by the intercalary vein of cell r 
<subScript id="5967201AFFEA392D1AE5FD8CFF53FDF2" attach="left" box="[160,168,601,615]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">3</subScript>
that is fainter in 
<taxonomicName id="02E359DCFFEA392D1B27FD92FE32FDF4" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityYear="1984" box="[354,457,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Macrurohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wirthi">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D1B27FD92FE82FDF5" box="[354,377,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D1BC2FD92FE32FDF4" box="[391,457,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">wirthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Males resemble males of 
<taxonomicName id="02E359DCFFEA392D18B6FD92FBCCFDF4" authority="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Grogan" authorityYear="1990" box="[755,1079,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Macrurohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D18B6FD92FCF1FDF5" box="[755,778,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D195DFD92FC9BFDF4" box="[792,864,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">similis</emphasis>
Spinelli &amp; Grogan
</taxonomicName>
, but in that species the posterior margin of sternite 9 is straight, the gonocoxite is curved, and the aedeagus is triangular, and its distal portion tapers to a moderately pointed tip. It is also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="02E359DCFFEA392D18C7FD5AFCFAFD3D" authority="Spinelli &amp; Ronderos &amp; Grogan, 2022" authorityName="Spinelli &amp; Ronderos &amp; Grogan" authorityYear="2022" box="[642,769,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Ceratopogonidae" genus="Macrurohelea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="morenoi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D18C7FD5AFD62FD3D" box="[642,665,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D18E3FD5AFCFAFD3D" box="[678,769,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">morenoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="F797FE4DFFEA392D194DFD5AFCBEFD3C" bold="true" box="[776,837,655,681]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="ECA44336FFEA392D194DFD5AFCBEFD3C" box="[776,837,655,681]" pageId="13" pageNumber="458" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but in that species the base of the aedeagus is broader than the bases of parameres and the distal portion is triangular and divided medially with apices slightly divergent, and the distal portion of parameres is stout, nearly straight and slightly divergent distally with rounded tips.
</paragraph>
